# Trade Capture Rules & Workflow Engine – Design Document

## 1. Overview

This document defines the architecture and implementation design for a scalable, deterministic, and auditable trade capture rules and workflow engine supporting:

- Economic rules (Trader-owned)
- Non-economic validation rules (Middle Office)
- Workflow orchestration rules (Tech Ops)

The system is designed to:
- Scale horizontally
- Support strict idempotency
- Enable deterministic replay (critical for regulatory compliance)
- Provide full auditability and explainability

---

## 2. Architectural Principles

### 2.1 Determinism
- Same input + same rule versions = identical output
- No runtime randomness or system-time dependencies

### 2.2 Separation of Concerns
- Rules ≠ Workflow ≠ Selection
- Each domain is independently versioned and governed

### 2.3 Immutability
- Rules and bundles are versioned and never mutated
- Trade binds to versions at execution time

### 2.4 Replayability
- Every trade event stores rule bundle versions
- Replay uses exact same versions

---

## 3. High-Level Architecture

text Trade Capture API       ↓ Idempotency Layer       ↓ Bundle Selection Engine       ↓ Rules Engine (Validation → Economic)       ↓ Persist Trade + Rule Context       ↓ Workflow Engine (DSL → Execution) 

---

## 4. Domain Separation

| Domain        | Owner         | Purpose                        |
|--------------|--------------|--------------------------------|
| Economic     | Traders       | Pricing, adjustments           |
| Validation   | Middle Office | Compliance, rejection rules    |
| Workflow     | Tech Ops      | Routing, orchestration         |

