## 5. DSL Design

### 5.1 Economic DSL

text RULE dividend_adjustment WHEN trade.dividend_yield > 0 THEN trade.adjusted_notional = trade.notional * (1 - trade.dividend_yield) 

Constraints:
- Pure functions only
- No external calls
- Deterministic execution

---

### 5.2 Validation DSL

text RULE restricted_counterparty WHEN trade.counterparty IN ["ABC","XYZ"] THEN REJECT "Restricted counterparty" 

Actions:
- REJECT
- FLAG
- WARN
- REQUIRE_APPROVAL

---

### 5.3 Workflow DSL

text FLOW trade_capture_flow STEP validate CALL validation_service STEP enrich CALL enrichment_service STEP send_ccp PUBLISH ccp_topic STEP wait_ccp WAIT_FOR ccp_ack timeout=5s STEP report PUBLISH reporting_topic 

---

## 6. Storage Model

### 6.1 rule_definition

Stores individual rules.

sql rule_id, rule_domain, version, rule_definition, status 

---

### 6.2 rule_bundle

Logical grouping of rules.

sql bundle_id, rule_domain, version, status 

---

### 6.3 rule_bundle_mapping

Maps rules to bundles.

sql bundle_id, bundle_version, rule_id, rule_version, execution_order 

---

### 6.4 trade_rule_context (CRITICAL)

Stores rule versions used for each trade event.

sql trade_id, event_version, economic_bundle, validation_bundle, workflow_bundle 

Purpose:
- Enables replay
- Enables audit

---

### 6.5 rule_execution_log

Execution trace.

sql trade_id, rule_id, version, outcome, message, executed_at 

---

### 6.6 workflow_definition

Stores workflow DSL and compiled IR.

sql flow_id, version, dsl_definition, compiled_ir 

---

## 7. Rule Execution Engine

### 7.1 Execution Flow

text Load bundle → compile DSL → cache AST → execute rules 

---

### 7.2 Core Components

- Parser (DSL → AST)
- Compiler (AST → executable)
- Execution Engine
- Cache layer

---

### 7.3 Execution Logic

java for (CompiledRule rule : rules) {     result = rule.execute(context);      if (result.action == REJECT) break; } 

---

### 7.4 Caching Strategy

- Cache compiled rules by bundle version
- No DB calls during execution
- Optional distributed cache (Hazelcast)

---

## 8. Dynamic Bundle Selection

### 8.1 Purpose

Select correct rule bundle based on trade attributes.

---

### 8.2 Selector Table

sql selector_id, domain, product_type, region, counterparty, min_notional, max_notional, bundle_id, bundle_version, priority, effective_from, effective_to 

---

### 8.3 Selection Algorithm

1. Filter matching selectors
2. Sort by:
   - priority DESC
   - specificity DESC
   - created_at DESC
   - selector_id ASC
3. Pick first

---

### 8.4 Specificity Scoring

text counterparty → +50 book         → +30 region       → +20 product      → +10 notional     → +5 

---

### 8.5 Conflict Handling

- Detect overlapping selectors at config time
- Reject ambiguous configurations

---

### 8.6 Persist Selection

text trade_rule_context ← selected bundle versions 

---

## 9. Workflow Execution (DSL → Runtime)

### 9.1 Approach

- DSL parsed into AST
- Converted to Intermediate Representation (IR)
- Executed via interpreter pattern

---

### 9.2 Execution Mapping

| DSL         | Runtime Mapping      |
|------------|---------------------|
| CALL        | Activity            |
| PUBLISH     | Activity            |
| WAIT_FOR    | Signal/Await        |
| IF          | Deterministic logic |

---

### 9.3 Key Constraints

- No direct I/O inside workflow logic
- All external calls via activities
- Deterministic branching only

---

## 10. Idempotency Design

### 10.1 Key

text idempotency_key = hash(source_id + version) 

---

### 10.2 Storage

- Redis (fast lookup)
- SQL (durable audit)

---

## 11. Replay Strategy

### 11.1 Process

text Fetch trade_rule_context Load same bundles Re-execute rules + workflow 

---

### 11.2 Guarantees

- Deterministic output
- Full audit trace

---

